Introduction

Base URL: http://api.moboeats.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Authentication Management

User API resource

Login through email and password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"edna.mann@example.net\",
    \"password\": \":e\\\"2K\\\\\",
    \"userType\": \"sit\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "edna.mann@example.net",
    "password": ":e\"2K\\",
    "userType": "sit"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Headers

The email of the user Example: edna.mann@example.net

The password of the user Example: :e"2K\

userType   string   

The type of user Example: sit

Registration

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"k\",
    \"email\": \"peffertz@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"QJK|kOqf\",
    \"userType\": \"aperiam\",
    \"phone\": \"a\",
    \"latitude\": \"iste\",
    \"longitude\": \"facere\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "k",
    "email": "peffertz@example.net",
    "password": "QJK|kOqf",
    "userType": "aperiam",
    "phone": "a",
    "latitude": "iste",
    "longitude": "facere"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

POST api/v1/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: k

email   string   

The email of the user Example: peffertz@example.net

password   string   

The password of the user Example: QJK|kOqf

userType   string   

The type of user Example: aperiam

otp   string  optional  
image   string  optional  
phone   string   

The type of user Example: a

latitude   string  optional  

optional The latitude of the user. Example -1.2847473 Example: iste

longitude   string  optional  

optional The longitude of the user. Example 36.3878745 Example: facere

Reset password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/reset-password" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"code\": \"sed\",
    \"password\": \"~B]rr-bqYB-o,o7\",
    \"password_confirmation\": \"nulla\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/reset-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "code": "sed",
    "password": "~B]rr-bqYB-o,o7",
    "password_confirmation": "nulla"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),

Get the authenticated user

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/user" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/user"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Create Rider Profile

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/rider/profile/create" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "vehicle_type=dolor" \
    --form "vehicle_license_plate=consequuntur" \
    --form "paypal_email=fmertz@example.net" \
    --form "vehicle_licesne_plate=aut" \
    --form "city=eum" \
    --form "state=eaque" \
    --form "postal_code=minus" \
    --form "profile_picture=@C:\Users\Lenovo\AppData\Local\Temp\php42B5.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://api.moboeats.test/api/v1/rider/profile/create"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('vehicle_type', 'dolor');
body.append('vehicle_license_plate', 'consequuntur');
body.append('paypal_email', 'fmertz@example.net');
body.append('vehicle_licesne_plate', 'aut');
body.append('city', 'eum');
body.append('state', 'eaque');
body.append('postal_code', 'minus');
body.append('profile_picture', document.querySelector('input[name="profile_picture"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());
